, so there is no need to merge these data set**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Next, i checked the number of subjects in the remaining datasets**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"n_distinct(Daily_activity$Id)\nn_distinct(Hourly_intensities$Id)\nn_distinct(Hourly_steps$Id)\nn_distinct(Sleep_day$Id)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-08-28T18:24:25.245754Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-08-28T18:24:25.247209Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-08-28T18:24:25.287921Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Daily_activity, Hourly_intensities y Hourly_steps tiene 33 participants mientras Sleep_day tiene 24 participantes.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"**Next,\tcheck and remove duplicates and NA**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"sum(duplicated(Daily_activity))\nsum(duplicated(Hourly_intensities))\nsum(duplicated(Hourly_steps))\nsum(duplicated(Sleep_day))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-08-28T18:30:29.221784Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-08-28T18:30:29.223180Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-08-28T18:30:29.338061Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Remove duplicates and NA","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"Daily_activity <- Daily_activity %>%\n  distinct() %>%\n  drop_na()\n  \nHourly_intensities <- Hourly_intensities %>%\n  distinct() %>%\n  drop_na()\n\nHourly_steps <- Hourly_steps %>%\n  distinct() %>%\n  drop_na()\n\nSleep_day <- Sleep_day %>%\n  distinct() %>%\n  drop_na()","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-08-28T18:36:02.657299Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-08-28T18:36:02.658788Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-08-28T18:36:02.685588Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"sum(duplicated(Sleep_day))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-08-28T18:36:13.361103Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-08-28T18:36:13.362699Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-08-28T18:36:13.378686Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Los duplicados en Sleep_day se ha removido","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Next,\tcheck the format of datetime and reformat for consistency","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"class(Daily_activity$ActivityDate)\nclass(Hourly_intensities$ActivityHour)\nclass(Hourly_steps$ActivityHour)\nclass(Sleep_day$SleepDay)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-08-28T18:37:22.068702Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-08-28T18:37:22.070049Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-08-28T18:37:22.112774Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"El tipo de dato en la fecha es de character, el formato debe ser cambiado","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"Daily_activity <- Daily_activity %>%\n  rename(date = ActivityDate) %>%\n  mutate(date=as.Date(date, format=\"%m/%d/%Y\"))\n\nSleep_day <- Sleep_day %>%\n  rename(date = SleepDay) %>%\n  mutate(date=as.Date(date, format=\"%m/%d/%Y %I:%M:%S %p\", tz=Sys.timezone()))\n","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-08-28T18:38:24.961782Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-08-28T18:38:24.963332Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-08-28T18:38:25.021134Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### **Volvemos a revisar la conherencia de los datos.**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"class(Daily_activity$ActivityDate)\nclass(Hourly_intensities$ActivityHour)\nclass(Hourly_steps$ActivityHour)\nclass(Sleep_day$SleepDay)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-08-28T18:39:17.729182Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-08-28T18:39:17.730684Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-08-28T18:39:17.755878Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"### **Revisamos las primeras 6 filas de las tablas Daily_activity y Sleep_day con la función head()**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"head(Daily_activity)\n\nhead(Sleep_day)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-08-28T18:39:23.771551Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-08-28T18:39:23.772969Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-08-28T18:39:23.822014Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"Hourly_intensities <- Hourly_intensities %>%\n  rename(date_time = ActivityHour) %>%\n  mutate(date_time = as.POSIXct(date_time, format=\"%m/%d/%Y %I:%M:%S %p\", tz=Sys.timezone()))\n\nHourly_steps <- Hourly_steps %>%\n  rename(date_time = ActivityHour) %>%\n  mutate(date_time = as.POSIXct(date_time, format=\"%m/%d/%Y %I:%M:%S %p\", tz=Sys.timezone()))","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-08-28T18:41:21.053934Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-08-28T18:41:21.055385Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-08-28T18:41:21.107142Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"Use head() to check:","metadata":{"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"head(Hourly_intensities)\n\nhead(Hourly_steps)","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2023-08-28T18:41:25.550716Z","iopub.execute_input":"2023-08-28T18:41:25.552108Z","iopub.status.idle":"2023-08-28T18:41:25.584481Z"},"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Next, the files are merged for analysis\n\n- Merge Daily_activity and Sleep_day, using Id and date as the primary key\n- Merge Hourly_intensities and Hourly_steps, using Id and datetime as the primary key","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"Daily_activity_sleep <- merge(Daily_activity, Sleep_day, by=c (\"Id\", \"date\"))\nHourly_intensities_steps <- merge(Hourly_intensities, Hourly_steps, by=c (\"Id\", \"date_time\"))","metadata":{"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Use head() to check:","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"head(Daily_activity_sleep)\n\nhead(Hourly_intensities_steps)","metadata":{"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## **ANALISIS Y VISUALIZACION**\n\nSplit Hourly_intensities_steps date_time into date and time","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"```{r}\nHourly_intensities_steps$Date <- format(as.POSIXct(Hourly_intensities_steps$date_time,format=\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\"), \"%Y-%m-%d\")\nHourly_intensities_steps$Time <- format(as.POSIXct(Hourly_intensities_steps$date_time,format=\"%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S\"), \"%H:%M:%S\")\n```","metadata":{"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"To look at the average steps and intensities throughout the day, plot steps and intensities over time","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"```{r}\nHourly_intensities_steps_ave <- Hourly_intensities_steps %>%\n  group_by(Time) %>%\n  summarize(average_steps = mean(StepTotal),\n    average_total_intensity = mean(TotalIntensity)) %>%\n  ggplot()+\n  geom_bar(mapping=aes(x = Time, y = average_steps, fill = average_total_intensity), stat=\"identity\")+\n  labs(title=\"Hourly steps and intensity over 24h\", x=\"Time\", y=\"average_steps\")+\n  scale_fill_gradient(low = \"yellow\", high = \"red\")+\n  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90))\n\nplot(Hourly_intensities_steps_ave)\n```","metadata":{"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"-\tSteps peaked between 12:00-14:00 and 17:00- 19:00, and intensity was the highest between 17:00-19:00\n-\tIt would be good to send notifications to introduce new workouts and/or high intensity workouts between 12:00-14:00 and 17:00- 19:00 where users are more likely to exercise\n-\tHourly reminder can also be sent to remind users to move around and take more steps in the morning (8:00-12:00) and in the evening (20:00- 22:00) where step counts are lower","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Next, take a look at the average steps taken over the days in a week for 33 subjects","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"```{r}\nDaily_activity_steps <- Daily_activity %>%\n  mutate(weekday = weekdays(date)) %>%\n  arrange(weekday) %>%\n  mutate(weekday = ordered(weekday, levels = c(\"Monday\", \"Tuesday\", \"Wednesday\", \"Thursday\", \"Friday\", \"Saturday\", \"Sunday\"))) %>%\n  group_by(weekday) %>%\n  summarize(average_steps = mean(TotalSteps))\n\nggplot(data = Daily_activity_steps)+\n  geom_bar(mapping=aes(x = weekday, y = average_steps), stat = \"identity\")+\n  labs(title=\"average steps per week\", x=\" \", y=\"average_steps\")+\n  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90))\n```","metadata":{"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"* The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention published that adult taking 8,000 step per day was associated with a 51% lower risk for all-cause mortality. https://www.cdc.gov/media/releases/2020/p0324-daily-step-count.html\n\n* Only 2 out of 7 days had above 8,000 steps per day. There is opportunity for Bellabeat to encourage their users to increase their daily number of steps. They can introduce reminders to users to move more when the hour is sedentary. They can also introduce a fun daily step challenge to encourage users to step up.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Next, I validated the correlation between total steps taken and calories burned","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"```{r}\nggplot(data=Daily_activity)+\ngeom_smooth(mapping=aes(x=TotalSteps, y=Calories))+\ngeom_point(mapping=aes(x=TotalSteps, y=Calories))+\nlabs(title=\"Total steps vs calories\")\n```","metadata":{"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"As expected, the results demonstrated a positive and linear correlation, which reinforces the importance of increasing the number of daily steps to increase physical activity which in turn increase calories burn","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"Next, I explored the correlation between minutes asleep versus Time in Bed and Total steps","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"ggplot(data=Daily_activity_sleep)+\ngeom_smooth(mapping=aes(x=TotalTimeInBed, y=TotalMinutesAsleep))+\ngeom_point(mapping=aes(x=TotalTimeInBed, y=TotalMinutesAsleep))+\nlabs(title=\"Total time in bed vs Total minutes asleep\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"code","source":"ggplot(data=Daily_activity_sleep)+\ngeom_smooth(mapping=aes(x=TotalSteps, y=TotalMinutesAsleep))+\ngeom_point(mapping=aes(x=TotalSteps, y=TotalMinutesAsleep))+\nlabs(title=\"Total steps vs Total minutes asleep\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"* There is a positive linear correlation between total time in bed and total minutes asleep, while zero correlation between total steps and total minutes asleep\n* Bellabeat app has a readiness and wellness scores that incorporates sleep analysis. To encourage users to get more sleep to enhance their readiness/wellness score to prepare for the next day, Bellabeat can consider to incorporate a notification feature to remind users to go to bed earlier","metadata":{}}]}